OL,6,FHelen and her young son, Ihor, spent
OL,7,Fprecious days together as a family
OL,8,Freunited with his father as he
OL,9,Frecovered from a shrapnel injury.
OL,11,FBut their time together was short, and
OL,12,FYura returned to fighting the
OL,13,Ffrontline in the Donetsk region in
OL,14,Feast Ukraine, a city that has seen
OL,15,Fsome of the bloodiest battles of the
OL,16,Fongoing conflict.
OL,18,FTwo months later, Helen received the
OL,19,Fnews she had been dreading. Yura had
OL,20,Fbeen killed in action in Bakhmut.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/12
